## 🚀 Lab Walkthrough

### Module 1 — Register Enterprise App + Configure SAML

This script creates the Azure AD Enterprise Application, configures SAML 2.0 SSO, generates a signing certificate, and assigns the lab group.

```powershell
.\scripts\powershell\01-AzureAD-SSO-Setup.ps1 `
    -TenantId        "your-tenant-id" `
    -AppDisplayName  "IAM-SSO-MFA-Lab" `
    -AssignmentGroup "SSO-Lab-Users" `
    -ReplyUrl        "https://sp.lab.local/simplesaml/module.php/saml/sp/saml2-acs.php/lab-sp" `
    -EntityId        "https://sp.lab.local"
```

**Screenshot — Azure AD App Registration:**

![Azure AD App Registration](screenshots/01-azure-app-registration.svg)

**What this does:**

- Registers an Application + Service Principal in Entra ID
- Sets `PreferredSingleSignOnMode = "saml"`
- Generates a 3-year RSA token signing certificate
- Assigns the `SSO-Lab-Users` security group
- Outputs federation metadata (SSO URL, Entity ID, cert thumbprint)

-----

### Module 2 — Conditional Access + MFA Enforcement

Creates three CA policies targeting the lab app:

|Policy                    |Scope                      |Grant                 |
|--------------------------|---------------------------|----------------------|
|`[LAB] Require MFA`       |All users, all client apps |Require MFA           |
|`[LAB] Block Legacy Auth` |All users, legacy protocols|Block                 |
|`[LAB] Risk-Based Step-Up`|Sign-in risk: Medium/High  |MFA + Compliant device|

```powershell
# Run in Report-Only mode first to validate impact
.\scripts\powershell\02-MFA-ConditionalAccess.ps1 `
    -TenantId      "your-tenant-id" `
    -TargetAppId   "your-app-client-id"

# Enable enforcement (remove report-only)
.\scripts\powershell\02-MFA-ConditionalAccess.ps1 `
    -TenantId      "your-tenant-id" `
    -TargetAppId   "your-app-client-id" `
    -EnablePolicies
```

**Screenshot — Conditional Access Policies:**

![Conditional Access Policies](screenshots/02-conditional-access-policy.svg)

> ⚠️ **Always run in Report-Only mode first.** Use **Entra ID → Security → Conditional Access → What If** to test policy impact before enabling.

-----

### Module 3 — Deploy the SAML SP (SimpleSAMLphp)

On your Ubuntu VM, run the SP setup script. This installs Apache, PHP, SimpleSAMLphp, generates the SP key pair, and configures the IdP remote metadata.

```bash
# Download the IdP signing certificate first
# From Entra: Enterprise Apps → IAM-SSO-MFA-Lab → SAML Certificates → Download (Base64)

sudo bash scripts/bash/setup-simplesamlphp-sp.sh \
    "https://sts.windows.net/your-tenant-id/" \
    "https://login.microsoftonline.com/your-tenant-id/saml2" \
    "./idp-signing.crt" \
    "sp.lab.local"
```

The script outputs:

- **SP Entity ID** → register in Azure AD as Identifier
- **SP ACS URL** → register in Azure AD as Reply URL
- **SP Metadata URL** → use for automatic registration
- **SP certificate** (Base64) → paste into Azure AD SAML signing config

